#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
msgid "Basic package management operations"
msgstr "Operações básicas de gestão de pacotes"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Basic package management operations on the Debian system can be performed by "
"any package management tools available on the Debian system.  Here, we "
"explain basic package management tools: <literal>apt-get</literal> / "
"<literal>apt-cache</literal> and <literal>aptitude</literal>."
msgstr ""
"As operações básicas de gestão de pacotes no sistema Debian podem ser "
"executas por qualquer ferramenta de gestão de pacotes disponível no sistema "
"Debian. Aqui vamos explicar as ferramentas de gestão básica de pacotes: "
"<literal>apt-get</literal> / <literal>apt-cache</literal> e "
"<literal>aptitude</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"For the package management operation which involves package installation or "
"updates package metadata, you need to have root privilege."
msgstr ""
"Para as operações de gestão de pacotes que envolvam a instalação ou "
"actualização de metadados do pacote, você precisa de ter privilégios de root."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> / <literal>apt-cache</literal> vs. "
"<literal>aptitude</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> / <literal>apt-cache</literal> contra o "
"<literal>aptitude</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The <literal>apt-get</literal> and <literal>apt-cache</literal> commands are "
"the most <emphasis role=\"strong\">basic</emphasis> package management tool."
msgstr ""
"Os comandos <literal>apt-get</literal> e <literal>apt-cache</literal> são as "
"ferramentas de gestão de pacotes mais <emphasis role=\"strong\">básicas</"
"emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> and <literal>apt-cache</literal> offer only the "
"commandline user interface."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> e o <literal>apt-cache</literal> oferecem "
"apenas a interface de linha de comandos."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> is most suitable for the <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">major system upgrade</emphasis> between releases, etc."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> é mais apropriado para a <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">actualização maior ao sistema</emphasis> entre lançamentos, etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> offers a <emphasis role=\"strong\">robust and "
"stable</emphasis> package resolver which uses the common package state data."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> oferece um resolvedor de pacotes <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">robusto e estável</emphasis> que usa dados de estado dos pacotes "
"comuns."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> has been updated to support autoinstall and "
"autoremove of recommended packages."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> foi actualizado para suportar a auto-instalação "
"e auto-remoção de pacotes recomendados."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> has been updated to support logging of package "
"activities."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> foi actualizado para suportar o registo em log "
"das actividades de pacotes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-cache</literal> offers a <emphasis role=\"strong\">standard</"
"emphasis> regex based search on the package name and description."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-cache</literal> oferece uma busca baseada em expressões "
"regulares <emphasis role=\"strong\">standard</emphasis> no nome do pacote e "
"na descrição."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>apt-get</literal> and <literal>apt-cache</literal> can manage "
"multiple versions of packages using <literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal> "
"but it is quite cumbersome."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>apt-get</literal> e o <literal>apt-cache</literal> podem gerir "
"múltiplas versões de pacotes usando o <literal>/etc/apt/preferences</"
"literal> mas fica bastante pesado."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The <literal>aptitude</literal> command is the most <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">versatile</emphasis> package management tool."
msgstr ""
"O comando <literal>aptitude</literal> é a ferramenta de gestão de pacotes "
"mais <emphasis role=\"strong\">versátil</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> offers the fullscreen interactive text user "
"interface."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> oferece a interface de utilizador de texto "
"interactiva de écran completo."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "<literal>aptitude</literal> offers the commandline user interface, too."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> também oferece uma interface de utilizador de "
"linha de comandos."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> is most suitable for the <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">daily interactive package management</emphasis> such as inspecting "
"installed packages and searching available packages."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> é mais apropriado para a <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">gestão de pacotes interactiva diária</emphasis> como o "
"inspeccionar os pacotes instalados e procurar pacotes disponíveis."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> offers an <emphasis role=\"strong\">enhanced</"
"emphasis> package resolver which also uses an extra package state data used "
"only by <literal>aptitude</literal>."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> oferece um resolvedor de pacotes <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">avançado</emphasis> que também usa uns dados de estado de "
"pacotes extra usados apenas pelo <literal>aptitude</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> supports autoinstall and autoremove of "
"recommended packages."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> suporta auto-instalação e auto-remoção de "
"pacotes recomendados."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "<literal>aptitude</literal> supports logging of package activities."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> suporta registo em log das actividades de "
"pacotes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> offers an <emphasis role=\"strong\">enhanced</"
"emphasis> regex based search on all of the package metadata."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> oferece um busca baseada em expressões "
"regulares <emphasis role=\"strong\">avançada</emphasis> em todos os "
"metadados dos pacotes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>aptitude</literal> can manage multiple versions of packages without "
"using <literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal> and it is quite intuitive."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>aptitude</literal> pode gerir múltiplas versões de pacotes sem "
"usar o <literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal> e é bastante intuitivo."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"Although the <literal>aptitude</literal> command comes with rich features "
"such as its enhanced package resolver, this complexity has caused (or may "
"still causes) some regressions such as <ulink url=\"&bugebbbcd;\">Bug "
"#411123</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&bugfbejda;\">Bug #514930</ulink>, and <ulink "
"url=\"&bugfhadhh;\">Bug #570377</ulink>.  In case of doubt, please use the "
"<literal>apt-get</literal> and <literal>apt-cache</literal> commands over "
"the <literal>aptitude</literal> command."
msgstr ""
"Apesar do comando <literal>aptitude</literal> vir com funcionalidades ricas "
"como o seu resolvedor avançado de pacotes, esta complexidade já causou (ou "
"pode ainda causar) algumas regressões como os <ulink url=\"&bugebbbcd;\">Bug "
"#411123</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&bugfbejda;\">Bug #514930</ulink>, e <ulink "
"url=\"&bugfhadhh;\">Bug #570377</ulink>. Em caso de dúvidas, por favor use "
"os comandos <literal>apt-get</literal> e <literal>apt-cache</literal> sobre "
"o comando <literal>aptitude</literal>."

