#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/sbin/init</literal>\" program is executed as the first "
"program and performs the main boot process. The Debian normally uses the "
"traditional sysvinit scheme with the <literal>sysv-rc</literal> package.  "
"See <literal>init</literal>(8), <literal>inittab</literal>(5), and "
"\"<literal>/usr/share/doc/sysv-rc/README.runlevels.gz</literal>\" for the "
"exact explanation.  This main boot process essentially goes through the "
"following."
