#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"In Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>, dependency based boot order provided "
"by the <literal>insserv</literal> package is used instead of classical "
"alphabetical one.  The \"<literal>CONCURRENCY</literal>\" value in "
"\"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" controls its concurrency: "
"\"<literal>none</literal>\" for no concurrency, \"<literal>startpar</literal>"
"\" for concurrency within the same sequence number, or \"<literal>makefile</"
"literal>\" for full concurrency.  See \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/insserv/"
"README.Debian</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"No Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>, é usada a ordem de arranque baseada em "
"dependências disponibilizada pelo pacote <literal>insserv</literal> em vez "
"da ordem alfabética clássica. O valor \"<literal>CONCURRENCY</literal>\" em "
"\"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" controla a sua concorrência. "
"\"<literal>none</literal>\" para nenhuma concorrência, \"<literal>startpar</"
"literal>\" para concorrência dentro do mesmo número de sequência, ou "
"\"<literal>makefile</literal>\" para concorrência total. Veja \"<literal>/"
"usr/share/doc/insserv/README.Debian</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The name of the symlink in each runlevel directory has the form "
"\"<literal>S&lt;2-digit-number&gt;&lt;original-name&gt;</literal>\" or "
"\"<literal>K&lt;2-digit-number&gt;&lt;original-name&gt;</literal>\". The 2-"
"digit-number is used to determine the order in which to run the scripts. "
"\"<literal>S</literal>\" is for \"Start\" and \"<literal>K</literal>\" is "
"for \"Kill\"."
msgstr ""
"O nome do link simbólico em cada directório runlevel tem o formato "
"\"<literal>S&lt;número-de-2-dígitos&gt;&lt;nome-original&gt;</literal>\" ou "
"\"<literal>K&lt;número-de-2-dígitos&gt;&lt;nome-original&gt;</literal>\". O "
"número-de-2-dígitos é usado para determinar a ordem sobre a qual correr os "
"scripts. \"<literal>S</literal>\" é para \"Start\" (iniciar) e \"<literal>K</"
"literal>\" é para \"Kill\" (terminar)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=none</literal>\", when <literal>init</literal>(8) "
"or <literal>telinit</literal>(8) commands goes into the runlevel to \"&lt;"
"n&gt;\", it execute following scripts."
msgstr ""
"Para \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=none</literal>\", quando os comandos "
"<literal>init</literal>(8) ou <literal>telinit</literal>(8) vão para o "
"runlevel para \"&lt;n&gt;\", executam os seguintes scripts."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The script names starting with a \"<literal>K</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/"
"rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" are executed in alphabetical order with the "
"single argument \"<literal>stop</literal>\". (killing services)"
msgstr ""
"Os scripts cujos nomes começam com um \"<literal>K</literal>\" em "
"\"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" são executados em ordem "
"alfabética com o único argumento \"<literal>stop</literal>\". (matando os "
"serviços)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The script names starting with an \"<literal>S</literal>\" in \"<literal>/"
"etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" are executed in alphabetical order with the "
"single argument \"<literal>start</literal>\". (starting services)"
msgstr ""
"Os scripts cujos nomes começam com um \"<literal>S</literal>\" em "
"\"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" são executados por ordem "
"alfabética com o único argumento \"<literal>start</literal>\". (iniciando os "
"serviços)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For example, if you had the links \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" and "
"\"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" in a runlevel directory, "
"\"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" which is symlinked to \"<literal>../init."
"d/sysklogd</literal>\" would run before \"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" "
"which is symlinked to \"<literal>../init.d/exim4</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Por exemplo, se você tiver os links \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" e "
"\"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" num directório de runlevel, o "
"\"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" que está simbolicamente ligado a "
"\"<literal>../init.d/sysklogd</literal>\" irá correr antes de "
"\"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" que está simbolicamente ligado a "
"\"<literal>../init.d/exim4</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=makefile</literal>\" (new default), package "
"dependency defined in the header of init scripts are used to order them."
msgstr ""
"Para \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=makefile</literal>\" (nova predefinição), a "
"dependência de pacotes definida no cabeçalho de scripts init é usada para as "
"ordenar."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
msgid ""
"It is not advisable to make any changes to symlinks in \"<literal>/etc/rcS.d/"
"</literal>\" unless you know better than the maintainer."
msgstr ""
"Não é aconselhável fazer quaisquer alterações nos links simbólicos em "
"\"<literal>/etc/rcS.d/</literal>\" a menos que você saiba mais que o "
"responsável."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "The runlevel management example"
msgstr "O exemplo de gestão do runlevel"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For example, let's set up runlevel system somewhat like <ulink url="
"\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> as the following."
msgstr ""
"Por exemplo, vamos configurar o sistema runleve algo como o <ulink url="
"\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "<literal>init</literal> starts the system in runlevel=3 as the default."
msgstr ""
"<literal>init</literal> arranca o sistema em runlevel=3 por predefinição"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>init</literal> does not start <literal>gdm</literal>(1) in runlevel="
"(0,1,2,6)."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>init</literal> não arranca o <literal>gdm</literal>(1) nos "
"runlevel (0,1,2,6)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>init</literal> starts <literal>gdm</literal>(1) in runlevel=(3,4,5)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>init</literal> arranca o <literal>gdm</literal>(1) em runlevel="
"(3,4,5)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"This can be done by using editor on the \"<literal>/etc/inittab</literal>\" "
"file to change starting runlevel and using user friendly runlevel management "
"tools such as <literal>sysv-rc-conf</literal> or <literal>bum</literal> to "
"edit the runlevel.  If you are to use command line only instead, here is how "
"you do it (after the default installation of the <literal>gdm</literal> "
"package and selecting it to be the choice of display manager)."
msgstr ""
"Isto pode ser feito ao usar o editor no ficheiro \"<literal>/etc/inittab</"
"literal>\" para alterar o runlevel de arranque e usar ferramentas de gestão "
"do runlevel amigas do utilizador como o <literal>sysv-rc-conf</literal> ou o "
"<literal>bum</literal> para editar o runlevel. Se você usar apenas a linha "
"de comandos, aqui está como fazê-lo (após a instalação predefinida do pacote "
"<literal>gdm</literal> e seleccioná-lo para ser o gestor de ecrã escolhido)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /etc/rc2.d ; mv S21gdm K21gdm\n"
"# cd /etc ; perl -i -p -e 's/^id:.:/id:3:/' inittab"
msgstr ""
"# cd /etc/rc2.d ; mv S21gdm K21gdm\n"
"# cd /etc ; perl -i -p -e 's/^id:.:/id:3:/' inittab"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Please note the \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" file "
"is checked when starting the display manager daemons: <literal>xdm</"
"literal>, <literal>gdm</literal>, <literal>kdm</literal>, and <literal>wdm</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""
"Por favor note que o ficheiro \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</"
"literal>\" é verificado quando se arranca daemons de gestor de ecrã: "
"<literal>xdm</literal>, <literal>gdm</literal>, <literal>kdm</literal>, e "
"<literal>wdm</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"You can still start X from any console shell with the <literal>startx</"
"literal>(1) command."
msgstr ""
"Você ainda pode arrancar o X a partir de qualquer consola de shell com o "
"comando <literal>startx</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "The default parameter for each init script"
msgstr "O parâmetro predefinido para cada script de init"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The default parameter for each init script in \"<literal>/etc/init.d/</"
"literal>\" is given by the corresponding file in \"<literal>/etc/default/</"
"literal>\" which contains environment variable assignments <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">only</emphasis>. This choice of directory name is specific to the "
"Debian system.  It is roughly the equivalent of the \"<literal>/etc/"
"sysconfig</literal>\" directory found in <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red "
"Hat Linux</ulink> and other distributions.  For example, \"<literal>/etc/"
"default/cron</literal>\" can be used to control how \"<literal>/etc/init.d/"
"cron</literal>\" works."
msgstr ""
"O parâmetro predefinido para cada script de init em \"<literal>/etc/init.d/</"
"literal>\" é dado pelo ficheiro correspondente em \"<literal>/etc/default/</"
"literal>\" o qual contém <emphasis role=\"strong\">apenas</emphasis> "
"atribuições das variáveis de ambiente. Esta escolha de nome de directório é "
"específica do sistema Debian. É grosseiramente o equivalente ao directório "
"\"<literal>/etc/sysconfig</literal>\" encontrado em <ulink url="
"\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> e outras distribuições. Por exemplo, "
"\"<literal>/etc/default/cron</literal>\" pode ser usado para controlar como "
"o \"<literal>/etc/init.d/cron</literal>\" funciona."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" file can be used to customize "
"boot-time defaults for <literal>motd</literal>(5), <literal>sulogin</literal>"
"(8), etc."
msgstr ""
"O ficheiro  \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" pode ser usado para "
"personalizar as predefinições no momento de arranque para <literal>motd</"
"literal>(5), <literal>sulogin</literal>(8), etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"If you cannot get the behavior you want by changing such variables then you "
"may <ulink url=\"&modifytheinitscripts;\">modify the init scripts</ulink> "
"themselves.  These are configuration files editable by system administrators."
msgstr ""
"Se não consegue obter o comportamento que deseja ao alterar tais variáveis "
"então você pode <ulink url=\"&modifytheinitscripts;\">modificar os scripts "
"de init</ulink>. Estes são ficheiros de configuração editáveis por "
"administradores de sistemas."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "The hostname"
msgstr "O nome da máquina"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The kernel maintains the system <emphasis role=\"strong\">hostname</"
"emphasis>.  The init script in runlevel S which is symlinked to \"<literal>/"
"etc/init.d/hostname.sh</literal>\" sets the system hostname at boot time "
"(using the <literal>hostname</literal> command) to the name stored in "
"\"<literal>/etc/hostname</literal>\".  This file should contain <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">only</emphasis> the system hostname, not a fully qualified "
"domain name."
msgstr ""
"O kernel mantém o <emphasis role=\"strong\">nome-de-máquina</emphasis> do "
"sistema. O script init em runlevel S which é ligado simbolicamente a "
"\"<literal>/etc/init.d/hostname.sh</literal>\" e define o nome de máquina "
"durante o arranque (usando o comando <literal>hostname</literal>) para o "
"nome armazenado em \"<literal>/etc/hostname</literal>\". Este ficheiro deve "
"conter <emphasis role=\"strong\">apenas</emphasis> o nome de máquina do "
"sistema, e não um nome de domínio totalmente qualificado."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"To print out the current hostname run <literal>hostname</literal>(1) without "
"an argument."
msgstr ""
"Para escrever o nome de máquina actual corra <literal>hostname</literal>(1) "
"sem argumentos."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "The filesystem"
msgstr "O sistema de ficheiros"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Although the root filesystem is mounted by the kernel when it is started, "
"other filesystems are mounted in the runlevel S by the following init "
"scripts."
msgstr ""
"Apesar do sistema de ficheiros raiz ser montado pelo kernel quando arranca, "
"outros sistemas de ficheiros são montados no runlevel S pelos seguintes "
"scripts de init."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountkernfs.sh</literal>\" for kernel filesystems in "
"\"<literal>/proc</literal>\", \"<literal>/sys</literal>\", etc."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountkernfs.sh</literal>\" para sistemas de "
"ficheiros do kernel em \"<literal>/proc</literal>\", \"<literal>/sys</"
"literal>\", etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountdevsubfs.sh</literal>\" for virtual filesystems "
"in \"<literal>/dev</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountdevsubfs.sh</literal>\" para sistemas de "
"ficheiros virtuais em \"<literal>/dev</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountall.sh</literal>\" for normal filesystems using "
"\"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountall.sh</literal>\" para sistemas de ficheiros "
"normais usando o \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountnfs.sh</literal>\" for network filesystems using"
"\"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountnfs.sh</literal>\" para sistemas de ficheiros "
"de rede usando o \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The mount options of the filesystem are set in \"<literal>/etc/fstab</"
"literal>\".  See <xref linkend=\"_optimization_of_filesystem_by_mount_options"
"\"/>."
msgstr ""
"As opções de montagem do sistema de ficheiros são definidas em \"<literal>/"
"etc/fstab</literal>\". Veja <xref linkend="
"\"_optimization_of_filesystem_by_mount_options\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"The actual mounting of network filesystems waits for the start of the "
"network interface."
msgstr ""
"A montagem actual de sistemas de ficheiros de rede espera que a interface de "
"rede arranque."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
msgid ""
"After mounting all the filesystems, temporary files in \"<literal>/tmp</"
"literal>\", \"<literal>/var/lock</literal>\", and \"<literal>/var/run</"
"literal>\" are cleaned for each boot up."
msgstr ""
"Após montar todos os sistemas de ficheiros, os ficheiros temporários em "
"\"<literal>/tmp</literal>\", \"<literal>/var/lock</literal>\", e \"<literal>/"
"var/run</literal>\" são limpos para cada arranque."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Network interface initialization"
msgstr "Inicialização da interface de rede"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Network interfaces are initialized in runlevel S by the init script "
"symlinked to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown-clean</literal>\" and "
"\"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown</literal>\".  See <xref linkend="
"\"_network_setup\"/> for how to configure them."
msgstr ""
"As interfaces de rede são iniciadas no runlevel 5 pelo script de init "
"simbolicamente ligado a \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown-clean</literal>\" e "
"\"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown</literal>\". Veja <xref linkend="
"\"_network_setup\"/> para como os configurar."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Network service initialization"
msgstr "Inicialização do serviço de rede"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Many network services (see <xref linkend=\"_network_applications\"/>) are "
"started under multi-user mode directly as daemon processes at boot time by "
"the init script, e.g., \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20exim4</literal>\" (for "
"RUNLEVEL=2) which is a symlink to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/exim4</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Muitos serviços de rede (veja <xref linkend=\"_network_applications\"/>) são "
"iniciados sob modo de multi-utilizador directamente como processos daemon "
"durante o arranque pelo script de init, ex., \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20exim4</"
"literal>\" (para RUNLEVEL=2) o que é um link simbólico para \"<literal>/etc/"
"init.d/exim4</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Some network services can be started on demand using the <ulink url="
"\"&superserver;\">super-server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> (or its "
"equivalents).  The <literal>inetd</literal> is started at boot time by "
"\"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20inetd</literal>\" (for RUNLEVEL=2) which is a "
"symlink to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/inetd</literal>\".  Essentially, "
"<literal>inetd</literal> allows one running daemon to invoke several others, "
"reducing load on the system."
msgstr ""
"Alguns serviços de rede podem ser iniciados a pedido usando o <ulink url="
"\"&superserver;\">super-servidor</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> (ou o seu "
"equivalente). O <literal>inetd</literal> é iniciado durante o arranque pelo "
"\"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20inetd</literal>\" (para RUNLEVEL=2) o qual é um "
"link simbólico para \"<literal>/etc/init.d/inetd</literal>\". "
"Essencialmente, o <literal>inetd</literal> permite que um daemon a correr "
"possa invocar vários outros, reduzindo a carga do sistema."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Whenever a request for service arrives at <ulink url=\"&superserver;\">super-"
"server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> , its protocol and service are "
"identified by looking them up in the databases in \"<literal>/etc/protocols</"
"literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/services</literal>\".  <literal>inetd</"
"literal> then looks up a normal Internet service in the \"<literal>/etc/"
"inetd.conf</literal>\" database, or a <ulink url="
"\"&opennetworkcompucalloncrpcsunrpc;\">Open Network Computing Remote "
"Procedure Call (ONC RPC)/Sun RPC</ulink> based service in \"<literal>/etc/"
"rpc.conf</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Sempre que um pedido para serviço chega ao <ulink url=\"&superserver;"
"\">super-servidor</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal>, o seu protocolo e "
"serviço é identificado ao procura-lo nas bases de dados em \"<literal>/etc/"
"protocols</literal>\" e \"<literal>/etc/services</literal>\". O "
"<literal>inetd</literal> então procura um serviço de Internet normal na base "
"de dados \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\", ou um serviço baseado em "
"<ulink url=\"&opennetworkcompucalloncrpcsunrpc;\">Open Network Computing "
"Remote Procedure Call (ONC RPC)/Sun RPC</ulink> em \"<literal>/etc/rpc.conf</"
"literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Sometimes, <literal>inetd</literal> does not start the intended server "
"directly but starts the <ulink url=\"&tcpwrapper;\">TCP wrapper</ulink> "
"program, <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), with the intended server name as its "
"argument in \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\".  In this case, "
"<literal>tcpd</literal> runs the appropriate server program after logging "
"the request and doing some additional checks using \"<literal>/etc/hosts."
"deny</literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/hosts.allow</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Por vezes, o <literal>inetd</literal> não arranca o servidor pretendido "
"directamente mas arranca o programa <ulink url=\"&tcpwrapper;\">wrapper de "
"TCP</ulink>, <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), com o nome do servidor pretendido "
"como seu argumento em \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\". Neste caso, o "
"<literal>tcpd</literal> corre o programa servidor apropriado após registar "
"em log o pedido e fazer algumas verificações adicionais usando \"<literal>/"
"etc/hosts.deny</literal>\" e \"<literal>/etc/hosts.allow</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For system security, disable as much network service programs as possible.  "
"See <xref linkend=\"_restricting_access_to_some_server_services\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Para segurança do sistema, desactive o máximo possível de programas de "
"serviço de rede. Veja <xref linkend="
"\"_restricting_access_to_some_server_services\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"See <literal>inetd</literal>(8), <literal>inetd.conf</literal>(5), "
