#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
msgid ""
"Do not use remote <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&ip;\">IP</"
"ulink> connection over <emphasis role=\"strong\">unsecured</emphasis> "
"network for X connection unless you have very good reason such as use of "
"encryption.  A remote TCP/IP socket connection without encryption is prone "
"to the <emphasis role=\"strong\">eavesdropping attack</emphasis> and is "
"disabled by default on the Debian system.  Use \"<literal>ssh -X</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Não use ligação <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&ip;\">IP</"
"ulink> remota sobre redes <emphasis role=\"strong\">inseguras</emphasis> "
"para ligação X a menos que tenha uma boa razão como o uso de encriptação. "
"Uma ligação socket TCP/IP remota sem encriptação é inclinada a <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">ataques de escuta</emphasis> e está desactivada por "
"predefinição no sistema Debian. Use \"<literal>ssh -X</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
msgid ""
"Do not use <ulink url=\"&xdmcpconnection;\">XDMCP connection</ulink> over "
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">unsecured</emphasis> network either.  It sends "
"data via <ulink url=\"&udp;\">UDP</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&ip;\">IP</ulink> "
"without encryption and is prone to the <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">eavesdropping attack</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Também não use <ulink url=\"&xdmcpconnection;\">ligação XDMCP</ulink> sobre "
"rede <emphasis role=\"strong\">insegura</emphasis>. Envia os dados via "
"<ulink url=\"&udp;\">UDP</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&ip;\">IP</ulink> sem "
"encriptação e é inclinado a <emphasis role=\"strong\">ataques de escuta</"
"emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can <emphasis role=\"strong\">dare</emphasis> to enable remote TCP/IP "
"connection by setting \"<literal>DisallowTCP=false</literal>\" in "
"\"<literal>/etc/gdm/gdm.conf</literal>\" to override \"<literal>/usr/share/"
"gdm/defaults.conf</literal>\" and by removing \"<literal>-nolisten</literal>"
"\" from lines found by \"<literal>find /etc/X11 -type f -print0 | xargs -0 "
"grep nolisten</literal>\", if you are in the fully <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">secured</emphasis> environment."
msgstr ""
"Você pode <emphasis role=\"strong\">atrever-se</emphasis> a activar a "
"ligação TCP/IP remota ao definir \"<literal>DisallowTCP=false</literal>\" em "
"\"<literal>/etc/gdm/gdm.conf</literal>\" para sobrepor \"<literal>/usr/share/"
"gdm/defaults.conf</literal>\" e ao remover \"<literal>-nolisten</literal>\" "
"da linhas encontradas por \"<literal>find /etc/X11 -type f -print0 | xargs "
"-0 grep nolisten</literal>\", se você está num ambiente completamente "
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">seguro</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"LTSP stands for <ulink url=\"&linuxterminalserverproject;\">Linux Terminal "
"Server Project</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"LTSP significa <ulink url=\"&linuxterminalserverproject;\">Linux Terminal "
"Server Project</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
msgid "Starting the X Window System"
msgstr "Iniciando o X Window System"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"The X Window System is usually started as an <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">X "
"session</ulink> which is the combination of an X server and connecting X "
"clients.  For the normal desktop system, both of them are executed on a "
"workstation."
msgstr ""
"O X Window System é geralmente iniciado como uma <ulink url=\"&xsession;"
"\">sessão X</ulink> a qual é a combinação de um servidor X e clientes X "
"ligados. Para o sistema de ambiente de trabalho normal, ambos são executados "
"numa estação de trabalho."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">X session</ulink> is started by the following."
msgstr ""
"A <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">sessão X</ulink> é iniciada com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "<literal>startx</literal> command started from the command line"
msgstr ""
"comando <literal>startx</literal> iniciado a partir da linha de comandos"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"One of the <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">X display manager</ulink> daemon "
"programs <literal>*dm</literal> started from the end of the start up script "
"in \"<literal>/etc/rc?.d/</literal>\" (\"<literal>?</literal>\" "
"corresponding to the runlevel) directory"
msgstr ""
"Um dos programas daemon de <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">gestor de ecrã "
"X</ulink> <literal>*dm</literal> arrancado a partir do fim do script de "
"arranque no directório \"<literal>/etc/rc?.d/</literal>\" (\"<literal>?</"
"literal>\" correspondendo ao runlevel)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"The start up script for the display manager daemons checks the content of "
"the \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" file before "
"actually executing themselves.  This ensures to have only one <ulink url="
"\"&xdisplaymanager;\">X display manager</ulink> daemon program activated."
msgstr ""
"O script de arranque para os daemons de gestão de ecrã verifica o conteúdo "
"do ficheiro \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" mesmo "
"antes de executar os próprios. Isto assegura que se tem apenas um programa "
"daemon de <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">gestor de ecrã X</ulink> activado."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"_specific_locale_only_under_x_window\"/> for initial "
"environment variables of the X display manager."
msgstr ""
"Veja <xref linkend=\"_specific_locale_only_under_x_window\"/> para as "
"variáveis de ambiente iniciais do gestor de écran X."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Essentially, all these programs execute the \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\" script.  Then the \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\" script "
"performs <literal>run-parts</literal>(8) like action to execute scripts in "
"the \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.d/</literal>\" directory. This is "
"essentially an execution of a first program which is found in the following "
"order with the <literal>exec</literal> builtin command."
msgstr ""
"Essencialmente, todos estes programas executam o script \"<literal>/etc/X11/"
"Xsession</literal>\". Então o script \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>"
"\" executa <literal>run-parts</literal>(8) como acção para executar os "
"scripts no directório \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.d/</literal>\". Isto é "
"essencialmente uma execução de um primeiro programa o qual é encontrado na "
"seguinte ordem com o comando embutido <literal>exec</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The script specified as the argument of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\" by the X display manager, if it is defined."
msgstr ""
"O script especificado como o argumento de <literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\" pelo gestor de display X, se estiver definido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.xsession</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>\" "
"script, if it is defined."
msgstr ""
"O script \"<literal>~/.xsession</literal>\" ou \"<literal>~/.Xsession</"
"literal>\", se estiver definido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-session-manager</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"O comando \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-session-manager</literal>\", se estiver "
"definido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-window-manager</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"O comando \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-window-manager</literal>\". se estiver "
"definido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-terminal-emulator</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"O comando \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-terminal-emulator</literal>\", se estiver "
"definido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"This process is affected by the content of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession."
"options</literal>\".  The exact programs to which these \"<literal>/usr/bin/"
"x-*</literal>\" commands point, are determined by the Debian alternative "
"system and changed by \"<literal>update-alternatives --config x-session-"
"manager</literal>\", etc."
msgstr ""
"Este processo é afectado pelo conteúdo de \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession."
"options</literal>\". Os programas exactos para os quais estes comandos "
"\"<literal>/usr/bin/x-*</literal>\" apontam são determinados pelo sistema de "
"alternativas Debian e modificados pelo \"<literal>update-alternatives --"
"config x-session-manager</literal>\", etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Starting X session with gdm"
msgstr "Iniciar uma sessão X com o gdm"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>gdm</literal>(1) lets you select the session type (or desktop "
