#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Customizing the X session (classic method)"
msgstr "Personalizar a sessão X (método clássico)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"On a system where \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.options</literal>\" contains "
"a line \"<literal>allow-user-xsession</literal>\" without preceding "
"\"<literal>#</literal>\" characters, any user who defines \"<literal>~/."
"xsession</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>\" is able to "
"customize the action of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\" by "
"completely overriding the system code. The last command in the \"<literal>~/."
"xsession</literal>\" file should use form of \"<literal>exec some-window/"
"session-manager</literal>\" to start your favorite X window/session managers."
msgstr ""
"Num sistema onde \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.options</literal>\" contém uma "
"linha \"<literal>allow-user-xsession</literal>\" sem o caractere "
"\"<literal>#</literal>\" a preceder, qualquer utilizador que defina "
"\"<literal>~/.xsession</literal>\" ou \"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>\" é "
"capaz de personalizar a acção de \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\" ao "
"sobrepor completamente o código do sistema. O último comando no ficheiro "
"\"<literal>~/.xsession</literal>\" deve usar a forma de \"<literal>exec some-"
"window/session-manager</literal>\" para iniciar os seus gestores de X window/"
"sessão favoritos."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Customizing the X session (new method)"
msgstr "Personalizar a sessão X (método novo)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Here are new methods to customize the X session without completely "
"overriding the system code as above."
msgstr ""
"Aqui estão alguns métodos de personalizar a sessão X sem sobrepor "
"completamente o código do sistema como em cima."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The display manager <literal>gdm</literal> can select a specific session and "
"set it as the argument of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"O gestor de écran <literal>gdm</literal> pode seleccionar uma sessão "
"específica e defini-la como o argumento de \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.xsessionrc</literal>\" file is executed as a part of start "
"up process. (desktop independent)"
msgstr ""
"O ficheiro \"<literal>~/.xsessionrc</literal>\" é executado como parte do "
"processo de arranque. (independente do ambiente de trabalho)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.gnomerc</literal>\" file is executed as a part of start up "
"process. (GNOME desktop only)"
msgstr ""
"O ficheiro \"<literal>~/.gnomerc</literal>\" é executado como parte do "
"processo de arranque. (apenas ambiente GNOME)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The GUI program based session management software may use the \"<literal>~/."
"gnome2/session</literal>\" file etc."
msgstr ""
"O software de gestão de sessão baseado em GUI pode usar o ficheiro "
"\"<literal>~/.gnome2/session</literal>\", etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Connecting a remote X client via SSH"
msgstr "Ligar um cliente X remoto via SSH"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The use of \"<literal>ssh -X</literal>\" enables a secure connection from a "
"local X server to a remote application server."
msgstr ""
"A utilização de \"<literal>ssh -X</literal>\" activa uma ligação segura de "
"um servidor X local a um servidor de aplicações remoto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Set \"<literal>X11Forwarding</literal>\" entries to \"<literal>yes</literal>"
"\" in \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" of the remote host, if you "
"want to avoid \"<literal>-X</literal>\" command-line option."
msgstr ""
"Defina as entradas \"<literal>X11Forwarding</literal>\" para \"<literal>yes</"
"literal>\" em \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" da máquina remota, "
"se deseja evitar a opção \"<literal>-X</literal>\" da linha de comando."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Start the X server on the local host."
msgstr "Arrancar o servidor X na máquina local."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Open an <literal>xterm</literal> in the local host."
msgstr "Abrir um <literal>xterm</literal> na máquina local."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Run <literal>ssh</literal>(1) to establish a connection with the remote site "
"as the following."
msgstr ""
"Correr o <literal>ssh</literal>(1) para estabelecer ligação com um site "
"remoto com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"localname @ localhost $ ssh -q -X loginname@remotehost.domain\n"
"Password:"
msgstr ""
"nome_local @ localhost $ ssh -q -X nome_de_login@domínio.máquina_remota\n"
"Palavra-passe:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Run an X application command, e.g. \"<literal>gimp</literal>\", on the "
"remote site as the following."
msgstr ""
"Correr um comando de aplicação X, ex. \"<literal>gimp</literal>\", no site "
"remoto com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "loginname @ remotehost $ gimp &amp;"
msgstr "nome_de_login @ máquina_remota $ gimp &amp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"This method can display the output from a remote X client as if it were "
"locally connected through a local UNIX domain socket."
msgstr ""
"Este método pode mostrar o resultado de um cliente X remoto como se ele "
"estivesse ligado localmente através de um socket de domínio UNIX local."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Secure X terminal via the Internet"
msgstr "Terminal X seguro via Internet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Secure X terminal via the Internet, which displays remotely run entire X "
"desktop environment, can easily achieved by using specialized package such "
"as <literal>ldm</literal>. Your local machine becomes a secure thin client "
"to the remote application server connected via SSH."
msgstr ""
"Terminal X seguro via Internet, o qual mostra um ambiente de trabalho X "
"completo a correr remotamente, pode ser conseguido facilmente usando um "
"pacote especializado como o <literal>ldm</literal>. A sua máquina local "
"torna-se num cliente magro seguro para um servidor de aplicações remoto "
"ligado via SSH."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"If you want to add similar feature to your normal display manager "
"<literal>gdm</literal>, create executable shell script at \"<literal>/usr/"
"local/bin/ssh-session</literal>\" as the following."
msgstr ""
"Se você deseja adicionar uma funcionalidade semelhante ao seu gestor de "
"écran <literal>gdm</literal> normal, crie um script de shell executável em "
"\"<literal>/usr/local/bin/ssh-session</literal>\" como o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#!/bin/sh -e\n"
"# Based on gdm-ssh-session in gdm source (GPL)\n"
"ZENITY=$(type -p zenity)\n"
"TARGETHOST=$($ZENITY --width=600 \\\n"
"--title \"Host to connect to\" --entry \\\n"
"--text \"Enter the name of the host you want to log in to as user@host.dom:\")\n"
"TARGETSESSION=$($ZENITY --width=600 --height=400 \\\n"
"--title \"Remote session name\" --list --radiolist --text \"Select one\" \\\n"
"--column \" \" --column \"Session\" --column \"description\" --print-column 2 \\\n"
"TRUE \"/etc/X11/Xsession\" \"Debian\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"/etc/X11/xinit/Xclients\" \"RH variants\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"gnome-session\" \"GNOME session\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"xterm\" \"Safe choice\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"rxvt\" \"Safe choice\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"gnome-terminal\" \"Safe choice\")\n"
"echo \"Connecting to \"$TARGETHOST\" with $TARGETSESSION\"\n"
"/usr/bin/ssh -A -X -T -n \"$TARGETHOST\" \"$TARGETSESSION\"\n"
"#SSH_ASKPASS=/usr/bin/ssh-askpass /usr/bin/ssh -A -X -T -n \"$TARGETHOST\" \"$TARGETSESSION\""
msgstr ""
"#!/bin/sh -e\n"
"# Based on gdm-ssh-session in gdm source (GPL)\n"
"ZENITY=$(type -p zenity)\n"
"TARGETHOST=$($ZENITY --width=600 \\\n"
"--title \"Host to connect to\" --entry \\\n"
"--text \"Enter the name of the host you want to log in to as user@host.dom:\")\n"
"TARGETSESSION=$($ZENITY --width=600 --height=400 \\\n"
"--title \"Remote session name\" --list --radiolist --text \"Select one\" \\\n"
"--column \" \" --column \"Session\" --column \"description\" --print-column 2 \\\n"
"TRUE \"/etc/X11/Xsession\" \"Debian\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"/etc/X11/xinit/Xclients\" \"RH variants\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"gnome-session\" \"GNOME session\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"xterm\" \"Safe choice\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"rxvt\" \"Safe choice\" \\\n"
"FALSE \"gnome-terminal\" \"Safe choice\")\n"
"echo \"Connecting to \"$TARGETHOST\" with $TARGETSESSION\"\n"
"/usr/bin/ssh -A -X -T -n \"$TARGETHOST\" \"$TARGETSESSION\"\n"
"#SSH_ASKPASS=/usr/bin/ssh-askpass /usr/bin/ssh -A -X -T -n \"$TARGETHOST\" \"$TARGETSESSION\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
