#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "<literal>unzip</literal>(1)"
msgstr "<literal>unzip</literal>(1)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&infozip;\">InfoZIP</ulink>: DOS unarchive and decompression "
"tool"
msgstr ""
"ulink url=\"&infozip;\">InfoZIP</ulink>: ferramenta de descompressão e de "
"desarquivar do DOS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
msgid ""
"Do not set the \"<literal>$TAPE</literal>\" variable unless you know what to "
"expect.  It changes <literal>tar</literal>(1) behavior."
msgstr ""
"Não defina a variável \"<literal>$TAPE</literal>\" a menos que saiba com o "
"que esperar. Altera o comportamento do <literal>tar</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"The gzipped <literal>tar</literal>(1) archive uses the file extension "
"\"<literal>.tgz</literal>\" or \"<literal>.tar.gz</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"O arquivo <literal>tar</literal>(1) gzipado usa a extensão de ficheiro "
"\"<literal>.tgz</literal>\" ou \"<literal>.tar.gz</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"The xz-compressed <literal>tar</literal>(1) archive uses the file extension "
"\"<literal>.txz</literal>\" or \"<literal>.tar.xz</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"O arquivo <literal>tar</literal>(1) comprimido em xz usa a extensão de "
"ficheiro \"<literal>.txz</literal>\" ou \"<literal>.tar.xz</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"Popular compression method in <ulink url=\"&foss;\">FOSS</ulink> tools such "
"as <literal>tar</literal>(1) has been moving as follows: <literal>gzip</"
"literal> → <literal>bzip2</literal> → <literal>xz</literal>"
msgstr ""
"Método de compressão popular em ferramentas <ulink url=\"&foss;\">FOSS</"
"ulink> tal como o <literal>tar</literal>(1) têm se movido como se segue: "
"<literal>gzip</literal> → <literal>bzip2</literal> → <literal>xz</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>cp</literal>(1), <literal>scp</literal>(1) and <literal>tar</"
"literal>(1) may have some limitation for special files.  <literal>cpio</"
"literal>(1) and <literal>afio</literal>(1) are most versatile."
msgstr ""
"<literal>cp</literal>(1), <literal>scp</literal>(1) e <literal>tar</literal>"
"(1) podem ter algumas limitações para ficheiros especiais. <literal>cpio</"
"literal>(1) e <literal>afio</literal>(1) são mais versáteis."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>cpio</literal>(1) and <literal>afio</literal>(1) are designed to be "
"used with <literal>find</literal>(1) and other commands and suitable for "
"creating backup scripts since the file selection part of the script can be "
"tested independently."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>cpio</literal>(1) e o <literal>afio</literal>(1) são desenhados "
"para serem usados com o <literal>find</literal>(1) e outros comandos e são "
"apropriados para criar scripts de backup pois a parte de selecção de "
"ficheiros do script pode ser testada independentemente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>afio</literal>(1) compresses each file in the archive.  This makes "
"<literal>afio</literal> to be much safer for the file corruption than the "
"globally compressed <literal>tar</literal> or <literal>cpio</literal> "
"archives and to be <emphasis role=\"strong\">the best archive engine</"
"emphasis> for the backup script."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>afio</literal>(1) comprime cada ficheiro num arquivo. Isto faz "
"com que o <literal>afio</literal> seja mais seguro contra corrupção de "
"ficheiros do que a compressão global dos arquivos <literal>tar</literal> ou "
"<literal>cpio</literal> e com que seja <emphasis role=\"strong\">o melhor "
"motor de arquivamento</emphasis> para scripts de backup."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"Internal structure of OpenOffice data files are \"<literal>.jar</literal>\" "
"file."
msgstr ""
"A estrutura interna dos ficheiros de dados do OpenOffice são ficheiros "
"\"<literal>.jar</literal>\"."

