#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Idioms for the archive"
msgstr "Idiomas para o arquivo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Here are several ways to archive and unarchive the entire content of the "
"directory \"<literal>./source</literal>\" using different tools."
msgstr ""
"Aqui estão várias maneiras de arquivar e \"desarquivar\" o conteúdo completo "
"do directório \"<literal>./source</literal>\" usando diferentes ferramentas."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "GNU <literal>tar</literal>(1):"
msgstr "GNU <literal>tar</literal>(1):"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ tar cvzf archive.tar.gz ./source\n"
"$ tar xvzf archive.tar.gz"
msgstr ""
"$ tar cvzf archive.tar.gz ./source\n"
"$ tar xvzf archive.tar.gz"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "<literal>cpio</literal>(1):"
msgstr "<literal>cpio</literal>(1):"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ find ./source -xdev -print0 | cpio -ov --null &gt; archive.cpio; gzip archive.cpio\n"
"$ zcat archive.cpio.gz | cpio -i"
msgstr ""
"$ find ./source -xdev -print0 | cpio -ov --null &gt; archive.cpio; gzip archive.cpio\n"
"$ zcat archive.cpio.gz | cpio -i"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "<literal>afio</literal>(1):"
msgstr "<literal>afio</literal>(1):"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ find ./source -xdev -print0 | afio -ovZ0 archive.afio\n"
"$ afio -ivZ archive.afio"
msgstr ""
"$ find ./source -xdev -print0 | afio -ovZ0 archive.afio\n"
"$ afio -ivZ archive.afio"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Idioms for the copy"
msgstr "Idiomas para a cópia"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Here are several ways to copy the entire content of the directory "
"\"<literal>./source</literal>\" using different tools."
msgstr ""
"Aqui estão algumas maneiras de copiar o conteúdo inteiro do directório "
"\"<literal>./source</literal>\" usando diferentes ferramentas."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Local copy: \"<literal>./source</literal>\" directory → \"<literal>/dest</"
"literal>\" directory"
msgstr ""
"Cópia local: directório \"<literal>./source</literal>\" → directório "
"\"<literal>/dest</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Remote copy: \"<literal>./source</literal>\" directory at local host → "
"\"<literal>/dest</literal>\" directory at \"<literal>user@host.dom</literal>"
"\" host"
msgstr ""
"Cópia remota: directório \"<literal>./source</literal>\" em máquina local → "
"directório \"<literal>/dest</literal>\" na máquina "
"\"<literal>utilizador@máquina.domínio</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "<literal>rsync</literal>(8):"
msgstr "<literal>rsync</literal>(8):"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd ./source; rsync -av . /dest\n"
"# cd ./source; rsync -av . user@host.dom:/dest"
msgstr ""
"# cd ./source; rsync -av . /dest\n"
"# cd ./source; rsync -av . utilizador@máquina.domínio:/dest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You can alternatively use \"a trailing slash on the source directory\" "
"syntax."
msgstr ""
"Você pode alternativamente usar a sintaxe de \"uma barra à direita no "
"directório fonte\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# rsync -av ./source/ /dest\n"
"# rsync -av ./source/ user@host.dom:/dest"
msgstr ""
"# rsync -av ./source/ /dest\n"
"# rsync -av ./source/ utilizador@máquina.domínio:/dest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "GNU <literal>cp</literal>(1) and openSSH <literal>scp</literal>(1):"
msgstr ""
"<literal>cp</literal>(1) de GNU e <literal>scp</literal>(1) de openSSH:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd ./source; cp -a . /dest\n"
"# cd ./source; scp -pr . user@host.dom:/dest"
msgstr ""
"# cd ./source; cp -a . /dest\n"
"# cd ./source; scp -pr . utilizador@máquina.domínio:/dest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# (cd ./source &amp;&amp; tar cf - . ) | (cd /dest &amp;&amp; tar xvfp - )\n"
"# (cd ./source &amp;&amp; tar cf - . ) | ssh user@host.dom '(cd /dest &amp;&amp; tar xvfp - )'"
msgstr ""
"# (cd ./source &amp;&amp; tar cf - . ) | (cd /dest &amp;&amp; tar xvfp - )\n"
"# (cd ./source &amp;&amp; tar cf - . ) | ssh utilizador@máquina.domínio '(cd /dest &amp;&amp; tar xvfp - )'"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# cd ./source; find . -print0 | cpio -pvdm --null --sparse /dest"
msgstr "# cd ./source; find . -print0 | cpio -pvdm --null --sparse /dest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# cd ./source; find . -print0 | afio -pv0a /dest"
msgstr "# cd ./source; find . -print0 | afio -pv0a /dest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You can substitude \"<literal>.</literal>\" with \"<literal>foo</literal>\" "
"for all examples containing \"<literal>.</literal>\" to copy files from "
"\"<literal>./source/foo</literal>\" directory to \"<literal>/dest/foo</"
"literal>\" directory."
msgstr ""
"Você pode substituir \"<literal>.</literal>\" por \"<literal>foo</literal>\" "
"para todos os exemplos que contêm \"<literal>.</literal>\" para copiar "
"ficheiros do directório \"<literal>./source/foo</literal>\" para o "
"directório \"<literal>/dest/foo</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You can substitude \"<literal>.</literal>\" with the absolute path "
"\"<literal>/path/to/source/foo</literal>\" for all examples containing "
"\"<literal>.</literal>\" to drop \"<literal>cd ./source;</literal>\".  These "
"copy files to different locations depending on tools used as follows."
msgstr ""
"Você pode substituir \"<literal>.</literal>\" pelo caminho absoluto "
"\"<literal>/caminho/para/fonte/foo</literal>\" para todos os exemplos que "
"contém \"<literal>.</literal>\" para abandonar \"<literal>cd ./source;</"
"literal>\". Estes copiam ficheiros para localizações diferentes dependendo "
"das ferramentas usadas como se segue."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>/dest/foo</literal>\": <literal>rsync</literal>(8), GNU "
"<literal>cp</literal>(1), and <literal>scp</literal>(1)"
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>/dest/foo</literal>\": <literal>rsync</literal>(8), <literal>cp</"
"literal>(1) do GNU, e <literal>scp</literal>(1)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>/dest/path/to/source/foo</literal>\": GNU <literal>tar</literal>"
"(1), <literal>cpio</literal>(1), and <literal>afio</literal>(1)"
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>/dest/path/to/source/foo</literal>\": <literal>tar</literal>(1) "
"do GNU, <literal>cpio</literal>(1), e <literal>afio</literal>(1)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>rsync</literal>(8) and GNU <literal>cp</literal>(1) have option "
"\"<literal>-u</literal>\" to skip files that are newer on the receiver."
msgstr ""
"<literal>rsync</literal>(8) e <literal>cp</literal>(1) do GNU têm a opção "
"\"<literal>-u</literal>\" para saltar ficheiros que são mais recentes no "
"receptor."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Idioms for the selection of files"
msgstr "Idiomas para a selecção de ficheiros"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>find</literal>(1) is used to select files for archive and copy "
"commands (see <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_archive\"/> and <xref linkend="
"\"_idioms_for_the_copy\"/>) or for <literal>xargs</literal>(1) (see <xref "
"linkend=\"_repeating_a_command_looping_over_files\"/>).  This can be "
"enhanced by using its command arguments."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>find</literal>(1) é usado para seleccionar ficheiros para o "
"arquivo e copiar comandos (veja <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_archive\"/> "
"e <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_copy\"/>) ou para <literal>xargs</literal>"
"(1) (veja <xref linkend=\"_repeating_a_command_looping_over_files\"/>). Isto "
"pode ser melhorado ao usar os seus argumentos de comando."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Basic syntax of <literal>find</literal>(1) can be summarized as the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"A sintaxe básica de <literal>find</literal>(1) pode ser sumariada no "
"seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Its conditional arguments are evaluated from left to right."
msgstr ""
"Os seus argumentos condicionais são avaliados da esquerda para a direita."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "This evaluation stops once its outcome is determined."
msgstr "Esta avaliação pára assim que o seu resultado é determinado."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"Logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">OR</emphasis>\" (specified by "
"\"<literal>-o</literal>\" between conditionals) has lower precedence than "
"\"logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">AND</emphasis>\" (specified by "
"\"<literal>-a</literal>\" or nothing between conditionals)."
msgstr ""
"O \"<emphasis role=\"strong\">OU</emphasis> lógico\" (especificado por "
"\"<literal>-o</literal>\" entre condicionais) tem precedência mais baixa que "
"o \"<emphasis role=\"strong\">E</emphasis> lógico\" (especificado por "
"\"<literal>-a</literal>\" ou nada entre condicionais)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"Logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">NOT</emphasis>\" (specified by "
"\"<literal>!</literal>\" before a conditional) has higher precedence than "
"\"logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">AND</emphasis>\"."
msgstr ""
"O \"<emphasis role=\"strong\">NÃO</emphasis> lógico\" (especificado por "
"\"<literal>!</literal>\" antes duma condicional) tem precedência mas alta "
"que o \"<emphasis role=\"strong\">E</emphasis> lógico\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-prune</literal>\" always returns logical <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">TRUE</emphasis> and, if it is a directory, searching of file is stopped "
"beyond this point."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-prune</literal>\" retorna sempre o <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">VERDADEIRO</emphasis> lógico e, se for um directório, a busca de ficheiro "
"é parada para além deste ponto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-name</literal>\" matches the base of the filename with shell "
"glob (see <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>) but it also matches its initial "
"\"<literal>.</literal>\" with metacharacters such as \"<literal>*</literal>"
"\" and \"<literal>?</literal>\". (New <ulink url=\"&posix;\">POSIX</ulink> "
"feature)"
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-name</literal>\" corresponde à base do nome de ficheiro com glob "
"de shell (veja <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>) mas também corresponde ao "
"seu \"<literal>.</literal>\" inicial com meta-caracteres como o "
"\"<literal>*</literal>\" e o \"<literal>?</literal>\". (Nova funcionalidade "
"do <ulink url=\"&posix;\">POSIX</ulink>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-regex</literal>\" matches the full path with emacs style "
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">BRE</emphasis> (see <xref linkend="
"\"_regular_expressions\"/>) as default."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-regex</literal>\" corresponde ao caminho completo com estilo "
"emacs <emphasis role=\"strong\">BRE</emphasis> (veja <xref linkend="
"\"_regular_expressions\"/>) como predefinição."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-size</literal>\" matches the file based on the file size (value "
"precedented with \"<literal>+</literal>\" for larger, precedented with "
"\"<literal>-</literal>\" for smaller)"
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-size</literal>\" corresponde ao ficheiro baseado no tamanho do "
"ficheiro (valor precedido de \"<literal>+</literal>\" para maior, precedido "
"de \"<literal>-</literal>\" para menor)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-newer</literal>\" matches the file newer than the one specified "
"in its argument."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-newer</literal>\" corresponde ao ficheiro mais recente que "
"aquele especificado no seu argumento."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>-print0</literal>\" always returns logical <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">TRUE</emphasis> and print the full filename (<ulink url=\"&nullterminated;"
"\">null terminated</ulink>) on the standard output."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>-print0</literal>\" retorna sempre o <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">TRUE</ emphasis> lógico e escreve o nome de ficheiro completo (<ulink url="
"\"&nullterminated;\">terminado em nulo</ulink>) na saída standard."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"<literal>find</literal>(1) is often used with an idiomatic style as the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>find</literal>(1) é usado geralmente com um estilo idiomático "
"como se segue."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# find /path/to \\\n"
"    -xdev -regextype posix-extended \\\n"
"    -type f -regex \".*\\.afio|.*~\" -prune -o \\\n"
"    -type d -regex \".*/\\.git\" -prune -o \\\n"
"    -type f -size +99M -prune -o \\\n"
"    -type f -newer /path/to/timestamp -print0"
msgstr ""
