"CVSROOT\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Checkout \"<literal>module1</literal>\" to its default directory "
"\"<literal>./module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Faça o checkout a \"<literal>module1</literal>\" para o seu directório "
"predefinido \"<literal>./module1</literal>\" com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co module1\n"
"$ cd module1"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/caminho/para\n"
"$ cvs co module1\n"
"$ cd module1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Make changes to the content as needed."
msgstr "Faça as alterações necessárias ao conteúdo."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Check changes by making \"<literal>diff -u [repository] [local]</literal>\" "
"equivalent by the following."
msgstr ""
"Verifique alterações ao fazer \"<literal>diff -u [repositório] [local]</"
"literal>\" equivalente ao seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs diff -u"
msgstr "$ cvs diff -u"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You find that you broke some file \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" "
"severely but other files are fine."
msgstr ""
"Você descobre que danificou o ficheiro \"<literal>ficheiro-a-desfazer</"
"literal>\" severamente mas os outros ficheiros estão bem."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Overwrite \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" file with the clean copy from "
"CVS by the following."
msgstr ""
"Sobrescreva o ficheiro \"<literal>ficheiro-a-desfazer</literal>\" com uma "
"cópia limpa do CVS com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -C file_to_undo"
msgstr "$ cvs up -C ficheiro-a-desfazer"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Save the updated local source tree to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Salva a árvore de fonte local actualizada para o CVS com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"Describe change\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"Descreve alteração\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create and add \"<literal>file_to_add</literal>\" file to CVS by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Crie e adicione o ficheiro \"<literal>ficheiro-a-adicionar</literal>\" ao "
"CVS com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ vi file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs add file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Added file_to_add\""
msgstr ""
"$ vi ficheiro-a-adicionar\n"
"$ cvs add ficheiro-a-adicionar\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"ficheiro-a-adicionar adicionado\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Merge the latest version from CVS by the following."
msgstr "Funda a versão mais recente do CVS com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Watch out for lines starting with \"<literal>C filename</literal>\" which "
"indicates conflicting changes."
msgstr ""
"Procure por linhas que comecem com \"<literal>C filename</literal>\" as "
"quais indicam alterações em conflito."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Look for unmodified code in \"<literal>.#filename.version</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Procura código não modificado em \"<literal>.#nome-ficheiro.versão</literal>"
"\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Search for \"<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>\" and "
"\"<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>\" in files for conflicting "
"changes."
msgstr ""
"Procura por \"<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>\" e "
"\"<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>\" em ficheiros por "
"alterações em conflito."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Edit files to fix conflicts as needed."
msgstr "Edite os ficheiros para corrigir os conflitos como necessário."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Add a release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Adicione uma etiqueta de lançamento \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" com o "
"seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"last commit for Release-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"última submissão para Release-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Release-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Edit further."
msgstr "Continuar a editar."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Remove the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Remova a etiqueta de lançamento \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" com o "
"seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag -d Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag -d Release-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Check in changes to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Verifique as alterações no CVS com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"real last commit for Release-1\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"última submissão real para Release-1\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Re-add the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" to updated CVS HEAD "
"of main by the following."
msgstr ""
"Re-adicione a etiqueta de lançamento \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" para o "
"CABEÇALHO CVS actualizado de main com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag Release-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create a branch with a sticky branch tag \"<literal>Release-initial-"
"bugfixes</literal>\" from the original version pointed by the tag "
"\"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" and check it out to \"<literal>~/path/"
"to/old</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr ""
"Crie um branch com uma etiqueta autocolante de branch \"<literal>Release-"
"initial-bugfixes</literal>\" a partir da versão original apontada pela "
"etiqueta \"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" e faça o check out para o "
"directório \"<literal>~/path/to/old</literal>\" com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Release-initial Release-initial-bugfixes module1\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co -r Release-initial-bugfixes -d old module1\n"
"$ cd old"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Release-initial Release-initial-bugfixes module1\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co -r Release-initial-bugfixes -d old module1\n"
"$ cd old"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Use \"<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>\" (<ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</"
"ulink> date format) instead of \"<literal>-r Release-initial</literal>\" to "
"specify particular date as the branch point."
msgstr ""
"Use \"<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>\" (formato de data <ulink url="
"\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink>) em vez de \"<literal>-r Release-initial</"
"literal>\" para especificar uma data particular como o ponto do branch."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Work on this local source tree having the sticky tag \"<literal>Release-"
"initial-bugfixes</literal>\" which is based on the original version."
msgstr ""
"Trabalhe nesta árvore de fonte local tendo a etiqueta autocolante "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" a qual é baseada na versão "
"original."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Work on this branch by yourself … until someone else joins to this "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch."
msgstr ""
"Trabalhe neste branch por si … até que alguém se junte a este branch "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Sync with files modified by others on this branch while creating new "
"directories as needed by the following."
msgstr ""
"Sincronize com ficheiros modificados por outros neste branch enquanto cria "
"novos directórios se necessário com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"checked into this branch\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"check feito para este branch\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Update the local tree by HEAD of main while removing sticky tag (\"<literal>-"
"A</literal>\") and without keyword expansion (\"<literal>-kk</literal>\") by "
"the following."
msgstr ""
"Actualize a árvore local pelo CABEÇALHO do main enquanto remove a etiqueta "
"autocolante (\"<literal>-A</literal>\") e sem a extensão de palavra chave "
"(\"<literal>-kk</literal>\") com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Update the local tree (content = HEAD of main) by merging from the "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch and without keyword "
"expansion by the following."
msgstr ""
"Actualize a árvore local (conteúdo = CABEÇALHO de main) ao fundir do branch "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" e sem a expansão palavra "
"chave com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Release-initial-bugfixes"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Release-initial-bugfixes"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Fix conflicts with editor."
msgstr "Corrigir conflitos com o editor."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"merged Release-initial-bugfixes\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"Release-initial-bugfixes fundido\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Make archive by the following."
msgstr "Criar arquivo com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv old old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ tar -cvzf old-module1-bugfixes.tar.gz old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ rm -rf old-module1-bugfixes"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv old old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ tar -cvzf old-module1-bugfixes.tar.gz old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ rm -rf old-module1-bugfixes"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>cvs up</literal>\" command can take \"<literal>-d</literal>\" "
"option to create new directories and \"<literal>-P</literal>\" option to "
"prune empty directories."
msgstr ""
"O comando \"<literal>cvs up</literal>\" pode receber a opção \"<literal>-d</"
"literal>\" para criar novos directórios e a opção \"<literal>-P</literal>\" "
"para suprimir os directórios vazios."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can checkout only a sub directory of \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by "
"providing its name as \"<literal>cvs co module1/subdir</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Você pode fazer checkout apenas a um sub directório de \"<literal>module1</"
"literal>\" ao fornecer o seu nome como \"<literal>cvs co module1/subdir</"
"literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
msgid ""
"Notable options for CVS commands (use as first argument(s) to <literal>cvs</"
"literal>(1))"
msgstr ""
"Opções notáveis para comandos CVS (use como primeiro argumento(s) para o "
"<literal>cvs</literal>(1))"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
msgid "option"
msgstr "opção"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "<literal>-n</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-n</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "dry run, no effect"
msgstr "nadar em 'seco', nenhum efeito"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "<literal>-t</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-t</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "display messages showing steps of cvs activity"
msgstr "mostra mensagens que mostram os passos da actividade do cvs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Latest files from CVS"
msgstr "Ficheiros mais recentes do CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"To get the latest files from CVS, use \"<literal>tomorrow</literal>\" by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Para obter os ficheiros mais recentes do CVS, use \"<literal>tomorrow</"
"literal>\" com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow module_name"
msgstr "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow nome-do-módulo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Administration of CVS"
msgstr "Administração do CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Add module alias \"<literal>mx</literal>\" to a CVS project (local server) "
"by the following."
msgstr ""
"Adicione o alias de módulo \"<literal>mx</literal>\" a um projecto de CVS "
"(servidor local) com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/modules\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a module1\" &gt;&gt;modules\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Now mx is an alias for module1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."
msgstr ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/modules\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a module1\" &gt;&gt;modules\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Agora mx é um alias para module1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Now, you can check out \"<literal>module1</literal>\" (alias: \"<literal>mx</"
"literal>\") from CVS to \"<literal>new</literal>\" directory by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Agora, você pode fazer check out ao \"<literal>module1</literal>\" (alias: "
"\"<literal>mx</literal>\") do CVS para o directório \"<literal>new</literal>"
"\" com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs co -d new mx\n"
"$ cd new"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs co -d new mx\n"
"$ cd new"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"In order to perform above procedure, you should have appropriate file "
"permissions."
msgstr ""
"De modo a executar o procedimento em cima, você precisa ter as permissões de "
"ficheiro apropriadas."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Execution bit for CVS checkout"
msgstr "Bit de execução para verificação do CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"When you checkout files from CVS, their execution permission bit is retained."
msgstr ""
"Quando você faz checkout a ficheiros de CVS, o seu bit de permissão de "
"execução é retido."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Whenever you see execution permission problems in a checked out file, e.g. "
"\"<literal>filename</literal>\", change its permission in the corresponding "
"CVS repository by the following to fix it."
msgstr ""
"Sempre que veja problemas com a permissão de execução num ficheiro a que fez "
"check out, ex. \"<literal>nome-de-ficheiro</literal>\", mude as suas "
"permissões no repositório CVS correspondente com o seguinte para a corrigir."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod ugo-x filename"
msgstr "# chmod ugo-x nome-de-ficheiro"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Subversion is a <emphasis role=\"strong\">recent-generation</emphasis> "
"version control system replacing older CVS.  It has most of CVS's features "
"except tags and branches."
msgstr ""
"Subversion é um sistema de controle de versão de <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">geração-recente</emphasis> que substitui o antigo CVS. Tem a maioria das "
"funcionalidades do CVS excepto as tags e branches."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"You need to install <literal>subversion</literal>, <literal>libapache2-svn</"
"literal> and <literal>subversion-tools</literal> packages to set up a "
"Subversion server."
msgstr ""
"Você precisa instalar os pacotes <literal>subversion</literal>, "
"<literal>libapache2-svn</literal> e <literal>subversion-tools</literal> para "
"configurar um servidor Subversion."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Configuration of Subversion repository"
msgstr "Configuração do repositório Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Currently, the <literal>subversion</literal> package does not set up a "
"repository, so one must set it up manually.  One possible location for a "
"repository is in \"<literal>/srv/svn/project</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Actualmente, o pacote <literal>subversion</literal> não configura um "
"repositório, então é preciso configurar um manualmente. Uma possível "
"localização para um repositório é em \"<literal>/srv/svn/project</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create a directory by the following."
msgstr "Crie um directório com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/project"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create the repository database by the following."
msgstr "Crie a base de dados do repositório com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/project"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Access to Subversion via Apache2 server"
msgstr "Acesso ao Subversion via servidor Apache2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"If you only access Subversion repository via Apache2 server, you just need "
"to make the repository only writable by the WWW server by the following."
msgstr ""
"Se você apenas aceder ao repositório Subversion via servidor Apache2, você "
"apenas precisa de activar a escrita no repositório pelo servidor WWW com o "
"seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/project"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Add (or uncomment) the following in \"<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-available/"
"dav_svn.conf</literal>\" to allow access to the repository via user "
"authentication."
msgstr ""
"Adicione (ou des-comente) o seguinte em \"<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-"
"available/dav_svn.conf</literal>\" para permitir o acesso ao repositório via "
"autenticação do utilizador."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;Location /project&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/project\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Subversion repository\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;Location /project&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/project\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Subversion repository\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create a user authentication file with the command by the following."
msgstr ""
"Crie um ficheiro de autenticação de utilizador com o comando com o seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd some-username"
msgstr "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd algum_nome_de_utilizador"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Restart Apache2."
msgstr "Reiniciar o Apache2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Your new Subversion repository is accessible at URL \"<literal>http://"
"localhost/project</literal>\" and \"<literal>http://example.com/project</"
"literal>\" from <literal>svn</literal>(1) (assuming your URL of web server "
"is \"<literal>http://example.com/</literal>\")."
msgstr ""
"O seu novo repositório Subversion está acessível no URL \"<literal>http://"
"localhost/project</literal>\" e \"<literal>http://exemplo.com/project</"
"literal>\" a partir de <literal>svn</literal>(1) (assumindo que o URL do seu "
"servidor web é \"<literal>http://exemplo.com/</literal>\")."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Local access to Subversion by group"
msgstr "Acesso local ao Subversion pelo grupo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The following sets up Subversion repository for the local access by a group, "
"e.g. <literal>project</literal>."
msgstr ""
"O seguinte configura um repositório Subversion para acesso local pelo grupo, "
"ex. <literal>project</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/project"
msgstr ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/project"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Your new Subversion repository is group accessible at URL \"<literal>file:///"
"localhost/srv/svn/project</literal>\" or \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</"
"literal>\" from <literal>svn</literal>(1) for local users belonging to "
"<literal>project</literal> group.  You must run commands, such as "
"<literal>svn</literal>, <literal>svnserve</literal>, <literal>svnlook</"
"literal>, and <literal>svnadmin</literal> under \"<literal>umask 002</"
"literal>\" to ensure group access."
msgstr ""
"O seu novo repositório Subversion está acessível ao grupo no URL "
"\"<literal>file:///localhost/srv/svn/project</literal>\" ou "
"\"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\" a partir de <literal>svn</"
